🐢 2. The Slow but Smart Turtle

In a green forest, animals were preparing for a big race. The rabbit, known for its speed, laughed loudly. “I’ll win easily!”

A turtle named Timo quietly joined the race. Everyone giggled. “You? You’re too slow!”

But Timo smiled. “Let’s see.”

The race began. The rabbit ran fast and quickly got ahead. Feeling confident, he stopped to rest under a tree. “I have plenty of time,” he said and fell asleep.

Meanwhile, Timo kept walking slowly but steadily. Step by step, he moved forward without stopping.

Hours passed. Timo finally reached the finish line — just as the rabbit woke up and ran as fast as he could. But it was too late.

The turtle had already won!

All the animals cheered. The rabbit felt embarrassed but learned a lesson.

Timo said gently, “Speed is good, but consistency wins.”

From that day, the rabbit never underestimated anyone again.

Moral: Slow and steady wins the race.